abstract: Hundreds of migrants seeking refuge from Middle East and Africa arrive in Vienna from Budapest in series of six trains and are greeted with supplies and cheers by welcoming residents; many migrants are intent on traveling on into Germany, and local officials make process of passing through Vienna and over border as easy as possible.
lead_paragraph: Arriving from Hungary, hundreds of determined migrants switched trains at the Westbahnhof rail station as they pressed on for Germany.

headline.main: In Vienna, Trains Packed With Refugees Are Welcomed and Ushered On
headline.print_headline: Welcomed in Vienna, Then Guided to the Door
